    primes = [2]
    for i in range(3, upper_bound, 2):
        if t[i]:
            continue
        primes.append(i)
        for j in range(i + i, upper_bound, i):
            t[j] = 1
    return primes

        d[a[l] - 1] = l
        d[a[r] - 1] = r
